      "created_at": "2025-05-28T13:27:08.521Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Oh sorry, I forgot to respond.  I really don\u2019t know.  I wanted to say zbike can have ERG issues as I remember some users contacting me with problems but I am not sure and google search did not show any issues.  This quietness of a spin bike is nice, probably durability is much longer but zwift+wahoo is such a standard in the performance biking world that would be my choice.  Now my guess is zbike might be more comfortable and have wider bike fit options so that might be a reason to go that route.  Also on either of these you still might want to stick your pedals on their for more accurate power reading.</p>",
