      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-05-29T06:29:04.052Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yep Zbike seems good.  Power meters in training devices are and especially smart bikes like this are just rough estimates. It looks like zbike is reasonably accurate but favero will likely be more accurate.  For me personally I don\u2019t care about total power accuracy that much meaning even if zbike reports too much and my FTP is too high this does not matter unless you are trying to compare it to outdoors and set targets for outdoor training.  So I agree you likely don\u2019t need them on the zbike and I likely would not use them but you might want to just try them to compare the power.</p>",
